<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41185a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41185a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41185a"> 185(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 3 distinct persons / (L.C. Dodgson &amp; X)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">This seemed to <font color="green">[L.C.]</font> horrible, and he invented a mild deception for use <font color="green">[in avoiding autograph-hunters or other pests]</font>. Through some <mark>third person</mark> he always represented that <mark>Lewis Carroll the author and Mr. Dodgson the professor were two distinct persons</mark>, and that he author could not be heard of at Oxford at all. <small> Miss Isa Bowman, <a name="IBSL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IBSL"><cite title="source">The Story Of Lewis Carroll</cite></a>. (1899) 14</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
